---
description: Tailwind styling conventions for randomfy v2 — cn(), NavLink, design tokens, globals utilities, and transitions. Apply when writing or reviewing JSX, CSS, or Tailwind classNames.
alwaysApply: true
---

## `cn()` ([`src/lib/cn.ts`](src/lib/cn.ts))

- Import `cn` from `@/lib/cn` (clsx + tailwind-merge).
- Every conditional or composite `className` must use `cn()`.
- Do not build Tailwind utility names with dynamic template literals (e.g. `text-${color}`) — breaks safelisting and merging.
- Do not stash Tailwind utilities in loose **string** variables; compose with `cn()` at the callsite. If the same composition repeats in one file, a module-level `const styles = cn(...)` is acceptable.

## Navigation links — `NavLink` ([`src/components/nav-link/nav-link.tsx`](src/components/nav-link/nav-link.tsx))

- Use `NavLink` for all internal navigation and external URLs. Do not duplicate link styling inline with raw `Link` / `<a>` + copied classes.
- Use the `external` prop for off-site links (`target="_blank"`, `rel="noopener noreferrer"`).
- Optional `preset`: `"nav-text"` (default) applies `.nav-text`; `"none"` passes through only `className` (e.g. header nav, custom typography).
- Optional `children`: when provided, renders instead of `label` (e.g. wordmark logo).

## Design tokens ([`tailwind.config.js`](tailwind.config.js))

- Spotify brand color: `text-brand`, `bg-brand`, `fill-brand`, `stroke-brand` (not ad-hoc hex or legacy names).
- Layout: `spacing.card` (300px), `grid-cols-auto-fit-card` where appropriate.
- `darkMode` is `class`.

## Globals utilities ([`src/app/globals.css`](src/app/globals.css))

- `@layer utilities`: `.nav-text`, `.text-display`, `.section-container`, `.icon-interactive` — prefer these over repeating the same utility bundles.

## Transitions

- Default pattern: `transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out`.
- Do not combine `ease-out` with `hover:ease-in` on the same element.

## Misc

- Avoid redundant `my-0` (vertical margin zero is the default).
